DISCLAIMER - EU CBAM COMPLIANCE

This software is a tool to assist with EU CBAM (Carbon Border Adjustment
Mechanism) reporting but does not constitute legal or compliance advice.

Users are responsible for:
- Ensuring compliance with applicable EU CBAM regulations
- Validating emission factors for their specific use case
- Verifying supplier data quality and certifications
- Consulting with legal/compliance experts as needed

The authors and copyright holders shall not be liable for any regulatory
compliance issues, penalties, or damages arising from the use of this software.

================================================================================

DATA ATTRIBUTION

This software uses emission factors from the following authoritative sources:

- International Energy Agency (IEA)
  Cement Technology Roadmap 2018
  https://www.iea.org/reports/technology-roadmap-low-carbon-transition-in-the-cement-industry

- Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC)
  Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories
  https://www.ipcc.ch/report/2006-ipcc-guidelines-for-national-greenhouse-gas-inventories/

- World Steel Association (WSA)
  Life Cycle Assessment Methodology Report
  https://worldsteel.org/steel-topics/sustainability/

- International Aluminium Institute (IAI)
  GHG Emissions Intensity Protocol
  https://international-aluminium.org/statistics/greenhouse-gas-emissions-intensity/

Users should cite these sources when using the emission factors in official
CBAM submissions.

